race.comment: BRIGIDINE GAL (9) finally gets to a race that suits at the fourth run of the campaign. Tackled stakes races either side of a 1400m BM78 in which she carried 59kgs against Saturday company. Beautifully in today for a dual Group 3 placegetter. CRISTAL CLEAR (1) has showed great determination to win at his last three outings, the latest in the Dubbo Cup over this distance under a steadier of 59kgs. Bonding well with Braith Nock who is aboard again. Can add to the picket fence back in Benchmark company. BROSNAN (8) settled midfield then let down impressively to just prevail over this course and distance recently. Up sharply in grade today but drops 6kgs. Cannot be underestimated. ZONDEE (7) put the writing on the wall last start when beaten just half a length over the Randwick mile. Only goes up 1kg tackling a midweeker so he gets his chance. JAMBEROO (5) will improve on what he does today but is worth throwing in wider exotics first-up from a spell.
